-- PRESS DIGEST - China - Aug 14
-- By Shanghai Newsroom
-- Wed Aug 13, 2014 09:48PM EDT
-- None



SHANGHAI, Aug 14 (Reuters) - Chinese newspapers available in Beijing and Shanghai carried the following stories on Thursday. Reuters has not checked the stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

CHINA SECURITIES JOURNAL - A document released by China's State Council on Wednesday laid out a blueprint to accelerate development of the country's insurance industry. The government said it would support insurance companies in developing innovative products in health, pension, agriculture and disaster, and allow these agencies to set up private-equity funds.   SHANGHAI SECURITIES NEWS - Shanghai released regulations to encourage comprehensive land development in the city's free trade zone (FTZ). Idle land parcels in the FTZ can be revalued and used for multi-purpose development. Industry experts believe companies in the FTZ with land development plans will benefit from the regulations.   CHINA DAILY - Shanghai Great Wisdom Co. Ltd <601519.SS>, a financial data provider, said it plans to purchase all of Xiangcai Securities Co Ltd, a securities brokerage firm listed in China's over-the-counter market for emerging enterprises. Market insiders said the 9 billion yuan ($1.46 billion) deal, if completed, would be the first instance of an internet-based data provider buying a brokerage firm and would mark a milestone in China's internet finance market.  PEOPLE'S DAILY - Communist Party members and cadres must adhere to the party's principles by earnestly listening to the public opinions; to adjust and make relevant changes based on the feedback, the newspaper, the mouthpiece of the ruling Communist Party of China, said in a commentary.